name: NSSpecifierTest.TestComparisonOperation
desc: These are passed to  init(objectSpecifier:comparisonOperator:test:) to specify the comparison operator.

items.name: case equal
items.desc: Binary comparison operator that results in true if the two objects are equal.

items.name: case lessThanOrEqual
items.desc: Binary comparison operator that results in true if the value of the test object is equal to or less than the value of the other object.

items.name: case lessThan
items.desc: Binary comparison operator that results in true if the value of the test object is less than the value of the other object.

items.name: case greaterThanOrEqual
items.desc: Binary comparison operator that results in true if the value of the test object is greater than or equal to the value of the other object.

items.name: case greaterThan
items.desc: Binary comparison operator that results in true if the value of the test object is greater than the value of the other object.

items.name: case beginsWith
items.desc: Binary containment operator that results in true if the test object is a list or string that matches the beginning of the other object (which is also a list or string).

items.name: case endsWith
items.desc: Binary containment operator that results in true if the test object is a list or string that matches the end of the other object (which is also a list or string).

items.name: case contains
items.desc: Binary containment operator that results in true if the test object is a list or string that matches the other object (which is also a list or string) at any location.
